'Dichlorine monoxide', Cl 2O, also known as 'oxygen dichloride',
'dichlorine oxide', or 'chlorine(I) oxide', is a chlorine oxide. It is a brownish-
yellow gas at room temperature which can explode in high concentrations when
exposed to heat or sparks. N. N. Greenwood and A. Earnshaw, "Chemistry of
the Elements", 2006 Butterworth-Heinemann
